## 2.4 Special Variants of Object Return

### Variant 1 тАФ Returning `this` (Self-Reference)

```java
class Counter {
    private int count = 0;
    public Counter increment() {
        count++;
        return this;   // returns the current object
    }
}
```
Used to enable **method chaining**: `c.increment().increment().increment();`

### Variant 2 тАФ Polymorphic Return (Covariant Return in Java)

```java
class Animal {
    public Animal reproduce() { return new Animal(); }
}
class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    public Dog reproduce() { return new Dog(); }   // covariant return тАФ legal in Java 5+
}
```

### Variant 3 тАФ Returning an Array of Objects

```java
public Student[] getToppers() {
    Student[] arr = { new Student("Anu", 95), new Student("Rahul", 92) };
    return arr;
}
```

### Variant 4 тАФ Returning from Static Factory Methods

```java
class Color {
    private Color(int r, int g, int b) { /*...*/ }
    public static Color red()   { return new Color(255, 0, 0); }
    public static Color green() { return new Color(0, 255, 0); }
}
```

