## 3.4 Problem 4 тАФ Returning an Array of Objects

**Problem Statement:**  
Write a method `getPassedStudents(Student[] all, int cutoff)` that returns a new array containing only those `Student` objects whose marks are тЙе cutoff.

### Step-by-Step Solution

**Step 1 тАФ Student Class (Simplified)**

```java
class Student {
    String name;
    int marks;
    public Student(String n, int m) { name = n; marks = m; }
}
```

**Step 2 тАФ Result Processor**

```java
public class ResultService {
    public static Student[] getPassedStudents(Student[] all, int cutoff) {
        // First pass тАФ count qualifying students
        int count = 0;
        for (Student s : all) if (s.marks >= cutoff) count++;

        // Allocate exact-size array
        Student[] result = new Student[count];

        // Second pass тАФ fill the result array
        int idx = 0;
        for (Student s : all) {
            if (s.marks >= cutoff) {
                result[idx++] = s;   // stores reference, not copy
            }
        }
        return result;   // <-- returns array reference
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student[] batch = {
            new Student("Anu", 88),
            new Student("Rahul", 45),
            new Student("Maya", 72),
            new Student("Kiran", 30)
        };
        Student[] passed = getPassedStudents(batch, 50);
        System.out.println("Passed students:");
        for (Student s : passed) System.out.println(s.name + " - " + s.marks);
    }
}
```

**Step 3 тАФ Output**

```
Passed students:
Anu - 88
Maya - 72
```

### Analytical Trace (Step Counts)

$$
n = \vert \text{batch} \vert = 4
$$

$$
\text{count} = \sum_{i=1}^{n} [\, s_i.\text{marks} \geq 50 \,] = 2 \quad (\text{Anu} = 88, \text{Maya} = 72)
$$

$$
\text{result array length} = 2, \quad \text{result} = \{\text{Anu}, \text{Maya}\}
$$

