## 3.6 Comparison Matrix тАФ When to Use Which Object Return Style

| Scenario | Best Return Style | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Single object creation logic | Direct object return (`return new X(...)`) | Encapsulation. |
| Need to chain calls | `return this;` | Fluent API / Builder. |
| Many subtypes possible | Interface return (`return new ConcreteX()`) | Polymorphism. |
| Reusable without instance | Static factory (`public static X create()`) | Naming constructors. |
| Returning a collection | Array or `ArrayList<>` | Bulk return. |
| Returning a *new* modified copy | Constructor-based return | Immutability. |

