## 1. Core Technical Definition & Intuitive Overview

### 1.1 Formal Academic Definition

In Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), a **Super Class** (also known as a **Parent Class**, **Base Class**, or **Superclass**) is the class whose members (attributes and methods) are **inherited** by another class. The class that inherits from a super class is termed the **Sub Class** (or derived class). Inheritance establishes an **"IS-A"** relationship, enforcing a strong hierarchical coupling between entities.

In Java, the `extends` keyword is the syntactic construct used to declare a super class relationship:

```java
class SubClass extends SuperClass {
    // inherits all non-private members of SuperClass
}
```

> [!NOTE]
> **KTU 2024 Syllabus Highlight:** Under the KTU 2024 scheme (NEP 2020), students are expected to articulate the difference between **Generalization** (bottom-up extraction of a super class) and **Specialization** (top-down derivation of a sub class). Both result in super class formation but arise from different design motivations.

### 1.2 Conceptual Analogy / Intuition

Think of a **Super Class** as a **biological parent** in a family tree.

- A father (super class) has traits like eye color, height tendency, and surname.
- A son (sub class) **inherits** these traits automatically тАФ he does not need to "redefine" his surname or eye color.
- However, the son (sub class) can also have his own unique traits (his own career, his own hobbies) that the father does not possess.
- If a son has the **same name** as his father (a "John" in the family), the son must use the keyword `super` to explicitly refer to the father's "John" тАФ otherwise, the son's own name shadows the father's.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Real-World Mapping:** A `Vehicle` super class with attributes `speed` and `capacity` is inherited by sub classes `Car`, `Truck`, and `Bus`. Every sub class automatically carries `speed` and `capacity` without rewriting them. This embodies the **DRY principle** (Don't Repeat Yourself) тАФ a high-yield concept frequently tested in KTU 2-mark/3-mark questions.

### 1.3 Physical / Logical Properties of a Super Class

| Property | Value / Behavior |
|---|---|
| Keyword to inherit | `extends` (Java), `:` (C++/C#), `(` `)` (Python) |
| Number of direct super classes allowed in Java | **Exactly 1** (Java does not support multiple class inheritance) |
| Constructors inherited? | **No** тАФ constructors are NOT members and are NEVER inherited |
| Private members inherited? | **Yes (logically)**, but **NOT accessible** directly in the sub class |
| Default super class of every Java class | `java.lang.Object` |

