> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Common Pitfalls:**
> 1. **Forgetting `super()` in parameterized constructor chains** тАФ Causes compilation failure. Always ensure either a no-arg parent constructor exists, or you explicitly call `super(args)`.
> 2. **Confusing `this()` with `super()`** тАФ `this()` calls another constructor in the **same** class; `super()` calls a constructor in the **parent** class. Both must be the first statement, so they cannot coexist in the same constructor.
> 3. **Assuming private members are not inherited** тАФ They ARE inherited but not accessible. This nuance is frequently asked in viva.
> 4. **Calling `super()` inside a static method** тАФ Compilation error. `super` requires an object context.
> 5. **Forgetting `@Override` annotation** тАФ Not a compile error, but KTU evaluators may deduct marks for lack of clarity in intent.

---

### ЁЯУМ Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- **Super class** = parent/base class; declared via `extends` in the sub class header.
- The keyword `extends` establishes the **IS-A** relationship.
- Java supports **single, multilevel, and hierarchical** inheritance тАФ **NOT multiple** inheritance via classes.
- The `super` keyword has **three uses**: `super.variable`, `super.method()`, and `super(args)`.
- `super()` (or `super(args)`) **must be the first statement** of a constructor.
- If omitted, the compiler inserts an implicit `super()` тАФ which fails if the parent has no no-arg constructor.
- **Constructors are NOT inherited**, but they are always chained.
- **Private members are inherited but NOT directly accessible** in the sub class.
- Every Java class implicitly extends `java.lang.Object`.
- The **execution order** of constructors in inheritance is: topmost ancestor тЖТ ... тЖТ immediate parent тЖТ current class.
- `final` classes **cannot** act as super classes (inheritance is blocked).
- Use `super.method()` to **extend** (not replace) the parent's overridden behavior тАФ core of the **Template Method** design pattern.
- Method overriding requires: same signature, covariant return type, access level not more restrictive, and no new checked exceptions.
- KTU 2024 emphasizes **NEP 2020 outcomes**: problem analysis, design thinking, and implementation тАФ so super class questions often blend inheritance with polymorphism and design patterns.

