### тЬЕ Question B (14 Marks) тАФ Adapter Pattern Focus

#### Part (a) тАФ 7 Marks
**[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023, Adapted]**
**Explain the Adapter design pattern with a real-world analogy. Identify and describe the four participants (GoF roles) in the pattern. Write a Java program demonstrating an Object Adapter that adapts a `USPlug` to an `IndianSocket` interface.**

**Model Answer:**

**Real-World Analogy:** A travel power adapter converts a US-style plug (round pins) to fit an Indian socket (large triangular holes). It doesn't change the electricity тАФ only the **physical interface**.

**Four GoF Participants:**

1. **Target (`IndianSocket`):** The interface the **Client** expects. Method: `providePower()`.
2. **Adaptee (`USPlug`):** The existing class with an incompatible interface. Method: `supplyUSCurrent()`.
3. **Adapter (`PlugAdapter`):** Implements Target, holds a reference to Adaptee, translates method calls.
4. **Client (`Charger`):** Uses the Target interface without knowing about the Adaptee.

**Java Program тАФ Object Adapter:**

```java
// Step 1: Target interface
interface IndianSocket {
    void providePower();
}

// Step 2: Adaptee (incompatible interface)
class USPlug {
    public void supplyUSCurrent() {
        System.out.println("Supplying 110V US current.");
    }
}

// Step 3: Adapter class (implements Target, holds Adaptee)
class PlugAdapter implements IndianSocket {
    private USPlug usPlug;  // Composition

    public PlugAdapter(USPlug usPlug) {
        this.usPlug = usPlug;
    }

    @Override
    public void providePower() {
        System.out.println("Adapter converting interface...");
        usPlug.supplyUSCurrent();  // Delegate to Adaptee
        System.out.println("Power delivered through Indian socket.");
    }
}

// Step 4: Client
class Charger {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        USPlug usPlug = new USPlug();
        IndianSocket adapter = new PlugAdapter(usPlug);
        adapter.providePower();  // Client uses Target interface only
    }
}
```

**Output:**
```
Adapter converting interface...
Supplying 110V US current.
Power delivered through Indian socket.
```

