## 2.2 KTU Formula / Cheat Sheet

> [!NOTE]
> The "formulas" in OOP design are **design heuristics** тАФ quantitative rules-of-thumb that express SOLID principles mathematically.

| Principle | Heuristic / "Formula" | Quantified Goal | Java Implementation Tool |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| **SRP** | $\text{Responsibilities per Class} \rightarrow 1$ | $\text{Actors served} = 1$ | Separate classes per actor |
| **OCP** | $\Delta \text{Behavior} = f(\text{new classes})$ | Modified lines per feature $\rightarrow 0$ in old code | `abstract` classes, polymorphism |
| **LSP** | $\forall s \in S, \ \text{Behavior}(s) \subseteq \text{Behavior}(T)$ | Subclass invariants $\supseteq$ parent invariants | `@Override` correctness, contracts |
| **ISP** | $\sum_{i=1}^{n} \text{Unused methods} \rightarrow 0$ | Interface methods used $\geq 1$ | Multiple small interfaces |
| **DIP** | $\text{Dep}(H) \cap \text{Dep}(L) = \emptyset$ (concrete) | Both depend only on `interface`/`abstract` | Constructor/setter injection |

**Real-world engineering utility:**
- **SRP** тЖТ Improves code review speed, parallel team development.
- **OCP** тЖТ Enables plugin architectures (e.g., Eclipse IDE, VSCode extensions).
- **LSP** тЖТ Critical for type-safe polymorphic collections (Java `List<T>`).
- **ISP** тЖТ Reduces JAR size and class-loader memory in Android/embedded Java.
- **DIP** тЖТ Backbone of Spring Framework's IoC container, JUnit's mocking framework.

