## 3.5 KeyEvent Handling тАФ Live Character Counter

> **Scenario:** Show how many characters are typed in a text field.

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class KeyDemo extends JFrame {
    JTextField textField;
    JLabel counterLabel;

    KeyDemo() {
        setTitle("Key Event Demo");
        setSize(400, 150);
        setLayout(new FlowLayout());
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        textField = new JTextField(20);
        counterLabel = new JLabel("Characters: 0");

        add(new JLabel("Type here:"));
        add(textField);
        add(counterLabel);

        textField.addKeyListener(new KeyAdapter() {
            public void keyTyped(KeyEvent e) {
                // Use keyTyped for character input
                counterLabel.setText("Characters: " + textField.getText().length());
            }
        });

        setVisible(true);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new KeyDemo();
    }
}
```

### Important Distinction for KTU

| Method | Returns | Best For |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `keyTyped()` | `getKeyChar()` works | Character input (letters, digits). |
| `keyPressed()` | `getKeyCode()` works | Non-character keys (F1, arrows, Shift). |
| `keyReleased()` | `getKeyCode()` works | Detecting key release (game controls). |

