## 3.6 MouseEvent Handling тАФ Drawing Coordinates

> **Scenario:** Display the (x, y) coordinates wherever the mouse is clicked on a panel.

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class MouseDemo extends JFrame {
    JLabel coordLabel;

    MouseDemo() {
        setTitle("Mouse Event Demo");
        setSize(500, 400);
        setLayout(new BorderLayout());
        setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        JPanel canvas = new JPanel();
        canvas.setBackground(Color.LIGHT_GRAY);
        coordLabel = new JLabel("Click anywhere on the panel");

        canvas.addMouseListener(new MouseAdapter() {
            public void mouseClicked(MouseEvent e) {
                int x = e.getX();
                int y = e.getY();
                coordLabel.setText("Clicked at: (" + x + ", " + y + ")");

                if (e.getClickCount() == 2) {
                    JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(MouseDemo.this, 
                        "Double-click detected at (" + x + ", " + y + ")");
                }
            }
        });

        add(canvas, BorderLayout.CENTER);
        add(coordLabel, BorderLayout.SOUTH);
        setVisible(true);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new MouseDemo();
    }
}
```

