### Model Solution for Q-B(b): 7 Marks

**Difference Table (3 marks):**

| Aspect | `keyPressed()` | `keyReleased()` | `keyTyped()` |
|--------|----------------|-----------------|--------------|
| **Trigger** | Key pushed down | Key let go | Unicode character generated |
| **`getKeyCode()`** | тЬЕ Returns valid code | тЬЕ Returns valid code | тЭМ Returns `VK_UNDEFINED` |
| **`getKeyChar()`** | тЭМ Returns `CHAR_UNDEFINED` | тЭМ Returns `CHAR_UNDEFINED` | тЬЕ Returns the typed character |
| **Best For** | Non-character keys (F1, Shift, arrows) | Game controls, shortcut detection | Reading text input |
| **Modifier keys** | Detected (Shift, Ctrl) | Detected | Not detected |

**Program (4 marks):**

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class EnterKeyDemo extends JFrame {
    EnterKeyDemo() {
        setTitle("Enter Key Focus Transfer");
        setSize(400, 200);
        setLayout(new FlowLayout());
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        JTextField field1 = new JTextField(15);
        JTextField field2 = new JTextField(15);
        JButton submitBtn = new JButton("Submit");

        add(new JLabel("Name:"));
        add(field1);
        add(new JLabel("Email:"));
        add(field2);
        add(submitBtn);

        field1.addKeyListener(new KeyAdapter() {
            public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {
                if (e.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_ENTER) {
                    field2.requestFocusInWindow();
                }
            }
        });

        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new EnterKeyDemo();
    }
}
```

**Key Points in Code:**
- `e.getKeyCode() == KeyEvent.VK_ENTER` is used inside `keyPressed()` because Enter is a non-character key.
- `requestFocusInWindow()` is the proper Swing way to shift focus (preferred over deprecated `requestFocus()`).

