## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mark-Deduction Traps in Event Handling Questions:**
> 
> 1. **Forgetting `setVisible(true)`** тАФ Program compiles and runs but no GUI appears. (Lose 1 mark)
> 2. **Using `getKeyChar()` in `keyPressed()`** тАФ Returns `CHAR_UNDEFINED` and your logic silently fails. (Lose 2 marks)
> 3. **Confusing `addActionListener` with `addMouseListener`** тАФ Wrong registration method = no event handling. (Lose 2 marks)
> 4. **Forgetting to extend `JFrame` and call `super()` in constructor** тАФ Causes null pointer exceptions. (Lose 1 mark)
> 5. **Not calling `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** тАФ Program hangs after closing window. (Lose 0.5 marks)
> 6. **Implementing adapter as interface** тАФ `MouseAdapter` is a **class**, not an interface. Use `extends`, not `implements`. (Lose 2 marks)
> 7. **Accessing local variables from anonymous classes without making them `final`** тАФ Compilation error in older Java. (Lose 1 mark)

