# 2. Deep Theoretical Analysis & KTU High-Yield Cheat Sheet

## 2.1 JFrame Class Constructors

`JFrame` provides four overloaded constructors. The **most commonly used** in KTU exam programs is the no-argument constructor.

| Constructor | Description | KTU Frequency |
|---|---|---|
| `JFrame()` | Creates a new, initially invisible window with no title | тШЕтШЕтШЕтШЕтШЕ |
| `JFrame(String title)` | Creates a new, initially invisible window with the given title | тШЕтШЕтШЕтШЕтШЕ |
| `JFrame(GraphicsConfiguration gc)` | Creates a window using the specified graphics configuration | тШЕ |
