## 2.3 The `WindowConstants` Exit Codes

`JFrame` implements `WindowConstants` which provides these integer constants тАФ **must be memorized** for exams:

| Constant | Value | Behavior on Close |
|---|---|---|
| `DO_NOTHING_ON_CLOSE` | `0` | Ignore the close click (window won't close) |
| `HIDE_ON_CLOSE` | `1` | Hide the window (default for `JDialog`/`JInternalFrame`) |
| `DISPOSE_ON_CLOSE` | `2` | Free window resources after closing |
| `EXIT_ON_CLOSE` | `3` | Terminate the JVM using `System.exit(0)` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Default Behavior**: If you forget to call `setDefaultCloseOperation()`, the default is `HIDE_ON_CLOSE` тАФ the window disappears but **the program keeps running in the background**. This is a classic KTU exam pitfall!

## 2.4 The Anatomy of a JFrame (Layered Architecture)

`JFrame` is NOT a single flat rectangle. It is a **multi-layered container** тАФ understanding this is critical for KTU board exams.

