## 3.3 Analytical Decision Tree: Choosing the Right `JTextField` Configuration

$$
\boxed{
\begin{aligned}
&\text{Is the input only one line?} \;\;\; \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \textbf{JTextField} \\
&\text{Is masking required?} \;\;\;\; \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \textbf{JPasswordField} \\
&\text{Is the field read-only?} \;\;\; \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \texttt{setEditable(false)} \\
&\text{Do you need a numeric spinner?} \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \textbf{JSpinner / JFormattedTextField} \\
&\text{Is it a search bar?} \;\;\;\; \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \text{JTextField} + \text{DocumentListener} \\
&\text{Need to validate format?} \;\;\; \rightarrow \text{Yes} \Rightarrow \text{JFormattedTextField} \\
\end{aligned}
}
$$

