### **Question 1** `[KTU University Exam - May 2024]`
**What is `JTextField` in Java? Write its class hierarchy.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

`JTextField` is a **lightweight Swing component** used to allow the user to **enter or edit a single line of unformatted text** in a GUI application. It is part of the `javax.swing` package and fires an `ActionEvent` when the user presses the **Enter key** while it has focus.

