### **Question 2** `[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]`
**Explain the difference between `setColumns(int)` and `setPreferredSize(Dimension)` for a `JTextField`.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

| Aspect | `setColumns(int)` | `setPreferredSize(Dimension)` |
|---|---|---|
| **Unit** | Number of character columns (integer) | Pixels (width ├Ч height) |
| **Layout-aware** | Yes тАФ recomputes on font/DPI change | No тАФ fixed pixel size |
| **Best practice** | **Recommended** by Swing guidelines | Avoid unless absolutely needed |
| **Effect on resize** | Field reflows with container | Field stays fixed |

`setColumns(n)` sets the field's **preferred width** in terms of character columns, allowing the layout manager to compute the actual pixel size based on the current font. `setPreferredSize()` locks the size in **absolute pixels**, which can cause visual issues on high-DPI displays or when the user changes the system font. Hence, for `JTextField`, **`setColumns()` is strongly preferred**. **(3 marks)**

