#### **Model Solution for (a):**

`JTextField` has **four constructors**:

1. `JTextField()` тАФ Creates an empty field with **0 columns** (auto width).
   ```java
   JTextField tf1 = new JTextField();
   ```

2. `JTextField(int columns)` тАФ Creates an empty field with the specified **column width**.
   ```java
   JTextField tf2 = new JTextField(20);
   ```

3. `JTextField(String text)` тАФ Creates a field **pre-filled** with the given text.
   ```java
   JTextField tf3 = new JTextField("Default text");
   ```

4. `JTextField(String text, int columns)` тАФ Pre-filled text **and** specified column width.
   ```java
   JTextField tf4 = new JTextField("Default", 20);
   ```

**Important methods:**

| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `setText(String t)` | Sets the field's content |
| `getText()` | Returns the current text |
| `setColumns(int n)` | Sets preferred width in columns |
| `setEditable(boolean b)` | Makes the field read-only or editable |
| `addActionListener(ActionListener l)` | Registers a listener for Enter-key events |
| `setHorizontalAlignment(int a)` | Aligns text (LEFT, CENTER, RIGHT) |
| `setEchoChar(char c)` | Masks input (for password fields) |
| `setActionCommand(String cmd)` | Sets the command string in `ActionEvent` |
| `setToolTipText(String s)` | Hover hint text |
| `setFont(Font f)` | Sets text font |
| `selectAll()` | Selects all text in the field |

**Example usage in a class:**
```java
JTextField name = new JTextField("Enter your name", 25);
name.setHorizontalAlignment(JTextField.CENTER);
name.setToolTipText("Type your full name here");
name.addActionListener(e -> System.out.println(name.getText()));
```

This creates a 25-column-wide centered field with placeholder-like text and a hover hint. **(7 marks)**

