> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Common Pitfalls:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting `addActionListener(this)`:** Many students define `actionPerformed` but forget to *register* it via `addActionListener`. The button will look clickable but nothing happens. тАФ **тИТ2 marks**
> 2. **Forgetting `setVisible(true)`:** The window opens but is invisible. Always call `setVisible(true)` at the **end** of the constructor. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 3. **Missing `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`:** The window closes visually but the JVM keeps running. KTU expects the proper close behavior. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 4. **Calling `parseInt` instead of `parseDouble`:** When decimals are involved (temperature, currency, scientific calculations), always use `Double.parseDouble()` to avoid `NumberFormatException`. тАФ **тИТ2 marks**
> 5. **Not handling `NumberFormatException`:** Input validation via `try-catch` is **mandatory** for any `parseXxx` call in exam code. тАФ **тИТ2 marks**
> 6. **Confusing `JTextField` with `JTextArea`:** If the question says "single-line input", use `JTextField`. If "multi-line", use `JTextArea`. Mixing them up loses concept marks. тАФ **тИТ2 marks**
> 7. **Not importing the right package:** `JTextField` is in `javax.swing`, not `java.awt`. Missing imports cause compilation errors. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 8. **Forgetting `implements ActionListener`:** If your class declares `actionPerformed` but doesn't `implements ActionListener`, the code won't compile. тАФ **тИТ2 marks**
> 9. **Using `==` for String comparison:** When comparing `getText()` output, always use `.equals()`, not `==`. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**
> 10. **Not setting layout:** Default `JFrame` uses `BorderLayout`. Without explicit `setLayout(new FlowLayout())`, components may stack weirdly. тАФ **тИТ1 mark**

