## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 JDBC Architecture тАФ The Layered Bridge

The following Mermaid diagram shows how a Java program interacts with a database through the JDBC API layers.

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    javaApp["Java Application Program"]
    jdbcAPI["JDBC API java sql Package"]
    driverMgr["DriverManager Class"]
    driverA["MySQL Driver Type 4"]
    driverB["Oracle Driver Type 4"]
    driverC["PostgreSQL Driver Type 4"]
    mysqlDB["MySQL Database Server"]
    oracleDB["Oracle Database Server"]
    postgresDB["PostgreSQL Database Server"]

    javaApp -->|"Calls DriverManager getConnection"| jdbcAPI
    jdbcAPI -->|"Selects Appropriate Driver"| driverMgr
    driverMgr -->|"Type 4 Thin"| driverA
    driverMgr -->|"Type 4 Thin"| driverB
    driverMgr -->|"Type 4 Thin"| driverC
    driverA -->|"TCP IP Protocol"| mysqlDB
    driverB -->|"TCP IP Protocol"| oracleDB
    driverC -->|"TCP IP Protocol"| postgresDB
```

### 4.2 CRUD Operation Pipeline тАФ Functional Flow

This block diagram traces a single CRUD cycle from program initiation to database persistence.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    start(["Program Start"]) --> load["Step 1 Load Driver Class"]
    load --> connect["Step 2 DriverManager getConnection"]
    connect --> create{"Step 3 Choose CRUD Operation"}

    create -->|"INSERT"| stmtCreate["PreparedStatement INSERT SQL"]
    create -->|"SELECT"| stmtRead["PreparedStatement SELECT SQL"]
    create -->|"UPDATE"| stmtUpdate["PreparedStatement UPDATE SQL"]
    create -->|"DELETE"| stmtDelete["PreparedStatement DELETE SQL"]

    stmtCreate --> execCreate["executeUpdate Returns row count"]
    stmtRead --> execRead["executeQuery Returns ResultSet"]
    stmtUpdate --> execUpdate["executeUpdate Returns row count"]
    stmtDelete --> execDelete["executeUpdate Returns row count"]

    execCreate --> persist["Rows Written to Database Table"]
    execRead --> display["Iterate rs next and Print Data"]
    execUpdate --> persist
    execDelete --> persist

    persist --> close["Step 4 Close Statement and Connection"]
    display --> close
    close --> finish(["Program End"])
```

### 4.3 Exception Handling Flow in JDBC

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    tryBlock["Try Block Open Connection Execute SQL"]
    tryBlock -->|"SQLException Thrown"| catchBlock["Catch SQLException e"]
    catchBlock --> printStack["e printStackTrace"]
    catchBlock --> log["Log Error to File"]
    catchBlock --> rollback["Rollback Transaction if needed"]

    tryBlock -->|"Success Path"| finallyBlock["Finally Block or try with resources"]
    finallyBlock --> closeConn["Close ResultSet Statement Connection"]
    closeConn --> end(["Resources Released Safely"])

    printStack --> end
    log --> end
    rollback --> end
```

