**Q.B. [KTU University Exam тАУ Dec 2023 тАФ Alternative Choice] тАФ (a) 7 Marks, (b) 7 Marks**

**(a)** With a neat diagram, explain the JDBC architecture. Differentiate between `Statement` and `PreparedStatement`.

**(b)** Write a Java program using JDBC to **update** the salary of all employees in the `employee` table by 10% who belong to department `'CSE'`. Then write a separate program to **delete** employees whose salary is less than тВ╣15,000. Use `try-with-resources` and `PreparedStatement`.

**Model Solution:**

**Part (a) тАФ JDBC Architecture + Comparison (7 Marks):**

JDBC Architecture consists of the following layers (refer to the Mermaid diagram in Section 4.1 of these notes):

- **Java Application Layer:** The user program that calls JDBC API methods.
- **JDBC API Layer:** The `java.sql` package providing interfaces such as `Connection`, `Statement`, `ResultSet`.
- **Driver Manager Layer:** Selects the appropriate database driver from registered drivers.
- **JDBC Driver Layer:** Vendor-specific implementation that translates JDBC calls into database-specific protocol.
- **Database Layer:** The actual RDBMS (MySQL, Oracle, etc.) that processes the SQL.

**Difference Table (3 marks):**

| Feature | `Statement` | `PreparedStatement` |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| SQL Type | Static | Parameterized |
| Pre-compiled | No | Yes |
| SQL Injection | Vulnerable | Safe |
| Performance | Slower for repeated use | Faster for repeated use |

*(2 marks diagram + 2 marks difference + 3 marks explanation = 7 marks.)*

**Part (b) тАФ UPDATE + DELETE (7 Marks):**

```java
import java.sql.*;

public class EmployeeMaintenance {
    static final String URL  = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/companydb";
    static final String USER = "root";
    static final String PASS = "password";

    public static void updateSalaries() {
        String sql = "UPDATE employee SET salary = salary * 1.10 WHERE department = ?";
        try (Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection(URL, USER, PASS);
             PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql)) {
            pst.setString(1, "CSE");
            int n = pst.executeUpdate();
            System.out.println(n + " CSE employee salaries updated by 10%.");
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    public static void deleteLowSalary() {
        String sql = "DELETE FROM employee WHERE salary < ?";
        try (Connection con = DriverManager.getConnection(URL, USER, PASS);
             PreparedStatement pst = con.prepareStatement(sql)) {
            pst.setDouble(1, 15000);
            int n = pst.executeUpdate();
            System.out.println(n + " employees deleted (salary < 15000).");
        } catch (SQLException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        updateSalaries();
        deleteLowSalary();
    }
}
```

*(3.5 marks for UPDATE code + 3.5 marks for DELETE code = 7 marks.)*

