> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Pitfalls тАФ Lose-Mark Callouts:**
> 1. **Using `executeQuery()` for `INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE`** тЖТ *Zero marks for the execution part.* Always check your method.
> 2. **Forgetting to close `Connection` / `Statement`** тЖТ Deduct 1 mark; KTU now expects `try-with-resources`.
> 3. **Hard-coding credentials inside the program** is acceptable in labs but never use `Class.forName()` errors silently тАФ always print the stack trace or rethrow.
> 4. **Wrong parameter index in `setXxx()`** (e.g., starting from 0 instead of 1) тАФ JDBC uses **1-based indexing**.
> 5. **Not handling `SQLException`** is an *unchecked-throws* error тАФ your code will not compile. Always wrap in `try-catch` or declare `throws`.

