## 3.6 Fine Calculation тАФ Worked Example

> Suppose a book is borrowed on **2024-01-01** and returned on **2024-01-20**.
> The standard loan period is **14 days**.

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{daysBorrowed} &= \text{ChronoUnit.DAYS.between}(2024\text{-}01\text{-}01,\; 2024\text{-}01\text{-}20) \\
                    &= 19 \text{ days} \\
\text{overdueDays}  &= \max(0,\; 19 - 14) = 5 \text{ days} \\
\text{fine}         &= 5 \times 2.00 = \mathbf{тВ╣10.00}
\end{aligned}
$$

This matches the runtime output:
```
Returned: [9780132350884] Clean Code by Robert Martin (Programming) - AVAILABLE | Fine: тВ╣10.0
```
