**Step-by-step implementation** *(full code is given in Section 3.4.5; here is the precise logic flow)*:

```java
public BorrowTransaction issueBook(String isbn, String userId) {
    // (1) Validate input
    if (isbn == null || userId == null) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("ISBN and userId are mandatory.");
    }
    // (2) Lookup user
    User user = searchUserById(userId);
    if (user == null) throw new UserNotFoundException(userId);
    // (3) Eligibility check
    if (user.getActiveLoanCount() >= 3) {
        throw new LoanLimitExceededException(userId);
    }
    // (4) Lookup and validate book
    Book book = searchByIsbn(isbn);
    if (book == null) throw new BookNotFoundException(isbn);
    book.markBorrowed();   // throws if not AVAILABLE
    // (5) Create and persist transaction
    String txnId = "TXN-" + LocalDate.now() + "-" + (++counter);
    BorrowTransaction txn = new BorrowTransaction(txnId, book, user);
    user.addBorrowedBook(book);
    // (6) SQL persistence
    db.executeUpdate("UPDATE BOOKS SET status='BORROWED' WHERE isbn=?", isbn);
    db.executeUpdate(
        "INSERT INTO TRANSACTIONS(transaction_id, isbn, user_id, borrow_date, due_date) "
      + "VALUES (?,?,?,?,?)",
        txnId, isbn, userId, txn.getBorrowDate(), txn.getDueDate());
    return txn;
}

public double returnBook(String isbn, String userId) {
    Book book = searchByIsbn(isbn);
    User user = searchUserById(userId);
    if (book == null || user == null) throw new IllegalArgumentException();
    BorrowTransaction txn = findOpenTransaction(user, book);
    if (txn == null) throw new IllegalStateException("No open transaction.");
    txn.closeTransaction();        // sets returnDate + computes fine
    book.markReturned();
    user.removeBorrowedBook(book);
    db.executeUpdate(
        "UPDATE TRANSACTIONS SET return_date=?, fine_amount=? WHERE transaction_id=?",
        txn.getReturnDate(), txn.getFine(), txn.getTransactionId());
    db.executeUpdate("UPDATE BOOKS SET status='AVAILABLE' WHERE isbn=?", isbn);
    return txn.getFine();
}
```

**Fine Calculation Worked Example (1 mark):**
For a book borrowed on 2024-01-01 and returned on 2024-01-20:
$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Days borrowed} &= 19 \\
\text{Overdue days}  &= 19 - 14 = 5 \\
\text{Fine}          &= 5 \times тВ╣2 = тВ╣10
\end{aligned}
$$

