#### Solution B(b) тАФ SQL Queries and Java Mapping **\[7 marks\]**

**(i) Overdue books (2 marks SQL + ┬╜ mark Java mapping):**

```sql
SELECT  b.isbn, b.title, t.user_id, t.due_date
FROM    TRANSACTIONS t
JOIN    BOOKS b ON t.isbn = b.isbn
WHERE   t.return_date IS NULL
  AND   t.due_date < CURRENT_DATE;
```

*Java mapping:* `Library.getOverdueBooks()` returns a `List<OverdueRecord>` DTO.

**(ii) Top-5 most-borrowed books (2 marks SQL + ┬╜ mark Java mapping):**

```sql
SELECT    b.isbn, b.title, COUNT(*) AS borrow_count
FROM      TRANSACTIONS t
JOIN      BOOKS b ON t.isbn = b.isbn
GROUP BY  b.isbn, b.title
ORDER BY  borrow_count DESC
LIMIT     5;
```

*Java mapping:* `Library.getTopBorrowedBooks(int n)` populates a `Map<String, Integer>` or DTO list.

**(iii) Total fine collected in a given month (2 marks SQL + 1 mark Java mapping):**

```sql
SELECT  COALESCE(SUM(fine_amount), 0) AS total_fine
FROM    TRANSACTIONS
WHERE   return_date BETWEEN '2024-01-01' AND '2024-01-31'
  AND   fine_amount > 0;
```

*Java mapping:*

```java
public double getTotalFineForMonth(int year, int month) {
    String sql = "SELECT COALESCE(SUM(fine_amount),0) FROM TRANSACTIONS "
               + "WHERE return_date BETWEEN ? AND ? AND fine_amount > 0";
    LocalDate start = LocalDate.of(year, month, 1);
    LocalDate end   = start.withDayOfMonth(start.lengthOfMonth());
    return db.executeQueryDouble(sql, start, end);
}
```

