## 1.3 Step-by-Step Design, Derivation & Source Code

### ЁЯзм Step 1 тАФ Class Blueprint (Design Document)

Before writing a single line of code, KTU's project evaluation rubric demands a **Design Document**. The class blueprint is derived as follows:

- **Identify the commonality:** Every payment has an *amount*, a *payer*, a *timestamp*, and an *action* called *process*. This is the **abstract super-class** `Payment`.
- **Identify the variations:** CreditCards need a card number and CVV; PayPal needs an email; Bank transfers need an account number and IFSC. These are the **concrete sub-classes**.
- **Identify the controller:** A `PaymentProcessor` that holds an *ArrayList* of mixed `Payment` objects and iterates over them calling the polymorphic method.

### ЁЯзм Step 2 тАФ Header Derivation (The Abstract Class)

The `Payment` class is declared `abstract` because it represents an *incomplete* concept тАФ you cannot "process a generic payment" without knowing the type. The methods are split into:

- **Abstract method** тЖТ `processPayment(double amount)` тЖТ *forces* every sub-class to provide its own logic.
- **Concrete method** тЖТ `validate()` тЖТ common to all; can be `final` to prevent accidental override.

```java
// File: Payment.java
import java.time.LocalDateTime;

public abstract class Payment {
    protected String payerName;
    protected double amount;
    protected LocalDateTime timestamp;

    public Payment(String payerName, double amount) {
        this.payerName = payerName;
        this.amount = amount;
        this.timestamp = LocalDateTime.now();
    }

    // ABSTRACT тАФ dynamic polymorphism hook
    public abstract boolean processPayment(double amount);

    // CONCRETE тАФ shared utility; final prevents override
    public final boolean validate() {
        if (amount <= 0) {
            System.out.println("[Validation] Invalid amount: " + amount);
            return false;
        }
        if (payerName == null || payerName.isEmpty()) {
            System.out.println("[Validation] Payer name missing.");
            return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

    public String getPayerName() { return payerName; }
    public double getAmount()    { return amount; }
    public LocalDateTime getTimestamp() { return timestamp; }

    public abstract String getPaymentDetails();
}
```

### ЁЯзм Step 3 тАФ Concrete Sub-Class Derivations

#### 3.1 `CreditCardPayment` (extends `Payment`)

- Inherits all common fields (`payerName`, `amount`, `timestamp`).
- Adds two private fields: `cardNumber`, `cvv`.
- Overrides `processPayment()` to perform card-luhn validation + 2% bank fee.
- Overrides `getPaymentDetails()` to mask the card number except the last 4 digits.

```java
// File: CreditCardPayment.java
public class CreditCardPayment extends Payment {
    private String cardNumber;
    private String cvv;

    public CreditCardPayment(String payerName, double amount,
                             String cardNumber, String cvv) {
        super(payerName, amount);
        this.cardNumber = cardNumber;
        this.cvv = cvv;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean processPayment(double amount) {
        if (!validate()) return false;
        if (cardNumber == null || cardNumber.length() != 16) {
            System.out.println("[CreditCard] Invalid card number length.");
            return false;
        }
        if (cvv == null || cvv.length() != 3) {
            System.out.println("[CreditCard] Invalid CVV.");
            return false;
        }
        double fee = amount * 0.02;
        double total = amount + fee;
        System.out.printf("[CreditCard] Charging %s -> Base: %.2f, Fee: %.2f, Total: %.2f%n",
                          maskCard(cardNumber), amount, fee, total);
        return true;
    }

    @Override
    public String getPaymentDetails() {
        return "CreditCard[" + maskCard(cardNumber) + "] for " + payerName;
    }

    private String maskCard(String card) {
        return "**** **** **** " + card.substring(card.length() - 4);
    }
}
```

#### 3.2 `PayPalPayment` (extends `Payment`)

