#### 3.3 `BankTransferPayment` (extends `Payment`)

- Adds `accountNumber` and `ifscCode` fields.
- Processing: validates IFSC format (11 characters), deducts a flat тВ╣10 fee.

```java
// File: BankTransferPayment.java
public class BankTransferPayment extends Payment {
    private String accountNumber;
    private String ifscCode;
    private static final double FLAT_FEE = 10.0;

    public BankTransferPayment(String payerName, double amount,
                               String accountNumber, String ifscCode) {
        super(payerName, amount);
        this.accountNumber = accountNumber;
        this.ifscCode = ifscCode;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean processPayment(double amount) {
        if (!validate()) return false;
        if (ifscCode == null || ifscCode.length() != 11) {
            System.out.println("[Bank] Invalid IFSC code (must be 11 chars).");
            return false;
        }
        double total = amount + FLAT_FEE;
        System.out.printf("[Bank] Debiting A/C %s -> Base: %.2f, Fee: %.2f, Total: %.2f%n",
                          maskAccount(accountNumber), amount, FLAT_FEE, total);
        return true;
    }

    @Override
    public String getPaymentDetails() {
        return "BankTransfer[Acct: " + maskAccount(accountNumber) +
               ", IFSC: " + ifscCode + "] for " + payerName;
    }

    private String maskAccount(String acc) {
        if (acc.length() < 4) return "****";
        return "******" + acc.substring(acc.length() - 4);
    }
}
```

### ЁЯзм Step 4 тАФ The Controller (`PaymentProcessor`)

The `PaymentProcessor` is the **driver class** that:
1. Maintains an `ArrayList<Payment>` тАФ a *heterogeneous* collection (Java generics with sub-type covariance in terms of polymorphism, even though the list itself is invariant, the elements are all `Payment`).
2. Exposes `addPaymentMethod(Payment p)` to register new methods.
3. Exposes `processAllPayments()` which iterates and **triggers dynamic polymorphism** with a single line: `p.processPayment(p.getAmount());`.

```java
// File: PaymentProcessor.java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class PaymentProcessor {
    private final List<Payment> paymentList = new ArrayList<>();

    // FUNCTIONALITY 1: Add Payment Method (polymorphic registration)
    public void addPaymentMethod(Payment payment) {
        if (payment == null) {
            System.out.println("[Processor] Cannot add null payment.");
            return;
        }
        paymentList.add(payment);
        System.out.println("[Processor] Added: " + payment.getPaymentDetails());
    }

    // FUNCTIONALITY 2: Process All (dynamic polymorphism in action)
    public void processAllPayments() {
        System.out.println("\n========== PROCESSING ALL PAYMENTS ==========");
        if (paymentList.isEmpty()) {
            System.out.println("[Processor] No payment methods registered.");
            return;
        }
        for (Payment p : paymentList) {
            // The line below is THE polymorphic call:
            //  -> JVM decides at run-time WHICH processPayment() to invoke
            boolean success = p.processPayment(p.getAmount());
            System.out.println("[Processor] Result: " + (success ? "SUCCESS" : "FAILED"));
            System.out.println("------------------------------------------");
        }
    }

    public int totalRegistered() {
        return paymentList.size();
    }
}
```

### ЁЯзм Step 5 тАФ The Main Demonstration

```java
// File: OnlinePaymentSystem.java  (Driver / Demo)
public class OnlinePaymentSystem {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        PaymentProcessor processor = new PaymentProcessor();

        // Register three DIFFERENT payment types via the COMMON super-type
        processor.addPaymentMethod(
            new CreditCardPayment("Arjun Sharma", 5000.00, "4111222233334444", "123")
        );
        processor.addPaymentMethod(
