**(a)** Design and implement an abstract class `Payment` in Java with fields `payerName` and `amount`, a constructor, a `final` method `validate()` that returns `true` only if `amount > 0` and `payerName` is not null/empty, and an abstract method `processPayment(double amount)`. **(7 marks)**

**(b)** Implement two concrete sub-classes тАФ `CreditCardPayment` and `PayPalPayment` тАФ both inheriting from `Payment`. Each must override `processPayment()` with its own fee logic (CreditCard: 2% fee; PayPal: 1.5% fee). Demonstrate dynamic polymorphism by creating a `PaymentProcessor` class that holds a `List<Payment>` and iterates calling `processPayment()`. **(7 marks)**

