##### **Model Solution:**

**(a) тАФ Compile-time vs Run-time polymorphism (7 marks):**

| Aspect | Compile-Time (Static) | Run-Time (Dynamic) |
|---|---|---|
| Mechanism | Method **overloading** | Method **overriding** |
| Resolution | Compiler decides based on argument types/signatures | JVM vtable decides based on actual object |
| Binding time | Compile time | Run time |
| Performance | Slightly faster (direct call) | Slightly slower (one indirection) |
| Example in project | `PaymentProcessor.addPaymentMethod(Payment p)` could be overloaded as `addPaymentMethod(CreditCardPayment c)` | `p.processPayment(amount)` where `p` is `Payment` reference but actual object is `CreditCardPayment` |

```java
// STATIC polymorphism example тАФ overloading in PaymentProcessor
public void addPaymentMethod(Payment p) { ... }                       // version 1
public void addPaymentMethod(List<Payment> batch) { ... }             // version 2 тАФ overload
```

```java
// DYNAMIC polymorphism example
Payment p = new CreditCardPayment(...);
p.processPayment(5000);   // JVM dispatches to CreditCardPayment.processPayment at run-time
```

