- тЬЕ Polymorphic methods **must** be `public` (or `protected`) and **non-static**, **non-final**, **non-private** тАФ otherwise dynamic dispatch is disabled.
- тЬЕ The sub-class constructor **must** call `super(...)` as its first statement if the super-class has a non-default constructor.
- тЬЕ A `List<Payment>` can hold `CreditCardPayment`, `PayPalPayment`, `BankTransferPayment` **simultaneously** тАФ this is *subtype polymorphism* in action.
- тЬЕ The line `for (Payment p : list) p.processPayment(amt);` is the **single line that proves dynamic polymorphism** тАФ one statement, many behaviours.
- тЬЕ Dynamic dispatch has **O(1)** complexity (constant time) due to the vtable indirection.
- тЬЕ Use `protected` for fields/methods that sub-classes need; use `private` for fields that should be fully encapsulated.
- тЬЕ **`final` methods cannot be overridden** тАФ useful for protecting critical shared logic (e.g., `validate()`).
- тЬЕ The project satisfies all four **OOP pillars**: Abstraction (abstract `Payment`), Inheritance (3 sub-classes), Polymorphism (overridden `processPayment`), Encapsulation (private fields + getters).
